{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017mZVhANNteQkoC7cFmGG8v","type":"tool_result","content":"2550\t    iteration 95's 473)\n2551\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n2552\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n2553\t- **Next**: `[engine] Dogpile + fraud queries` — 7 unchecked items\n2554\t  remain in the Implementation Checklist.\n2555\t- **Log**: iteration-096.log\n2556\t## Iteration 96 — 2026-04-26T06:20:30Z — OK\n2557\t- **Log**: iteration-096.log\n2558\t\n2559\t\n2560\t\n2561\t## Iteration 97 — 2026-04-26 — OK\n2562\t- **Item**: `[engine] Dogpile + fraud queries: dogpile_events (scheduled/active/ended/cancelled with linked campaigns/game_entries/point_grants) + fraud_flags (open/reviewed/dismissed read-only).`\n2563\t- **Files added** (1):\n2564\t  - `peek/src/server/db/queries/get-dogpile-and-fraud.ts` — three exports\n2565\t    matching the FR-9 read-only contract:\n2566\t    - `listDogpileEvents` reads `dogpile_events` with optional `status`\n2567\t      ('scheduled' / 'active' / 'ended' / 'cancelled') + `startsFrom` /\n2568\t      `startsTo` filters, left-joins `campaigns` for the parent campaign\n2569\t      name + type (campaign_id is nullable), and annotates each row with\n2570\t      scalar-subquery counts of `game_entries` and `point_grants` whose\n2571\t      `created_at` falls within the event's `[starts_at, ends_at)`\n2572\t      window. There is no FK from those ledgers to `dogpile_events`; the\n2573\t      points-grant queue handler (`backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts`)\n2574\t      applies the multiplier purely by time-window match, so a window count\n2575\t      is the closest operator-meaningful \"linked\" set the spec calls for.\n2576\t    - `listFraudFlags` reads `fraud_flags` with optional `status`\n2577\t      ('open' / 'reviewed' / 'dismissed') + `userId` + `flagType` +\n2578\t      `createdFrom` / `createdTo` filters, left-joins `player_profiles`\n2579\t      for username + wallet context, and round-trips the JSONB `details`\n2580\t      column verbatim so the operator UI can show whatever metadata the\n2581\t      writer attached. Order is `open → reviewed → dismissed` then\n2582\t      `created_at desc` so the review queue surfaces the actionable rows\n2583\t      first.\n2584\t    - `getDogpileFraudOverview` produces the FR-4 metric strip:\n2585\t      scheduled count, active count, ended-in-window count, cancelled-in-\n2586\t      window count, open fraud-flag count. Window defaults to 24h\n2587\t      (`PEEK_DOGPILE_FRAUD_OVERVIEW_WINDOW_HOURS = 24`); five queries fan\n2588\t      out via `Promise.all`. Each metric carries the FR-4 bookkeeping\n2589\t      (id, label, value, source table, window label, \"as of\",\n2590\t      definition, drilldown href).\n2591\t- **Files updated** (1):\n2592\t  - `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts` — added the FR-9 dogpile + fraud view\n2593\t    models alongside the existing challenge engine block:\n2594\t    `PeekDogpileStatus` + `PEEK_DOGPILE_STATUSES`, `PeekDogpileEventRow`,\n2595\t    `PeekDogpileEventFilters`, `PeekFraudFlagListRow` (extends the\n2596\t    existing per-user `PeekFraudFlagRow` shape with the username + wallet +\n2597\t    JSONB details columns the global fraud table needs),\n2598\t    `PeekFraudFlagFilters`, `PeekDogpileFraudOverviewMetricId` +\n2599\t    `PEEK_DOGPILE_FRAUD_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS`, `PeekDogpileFraudOverview`.\n2600\t    Status / flag-type values stay loosely typed (`string`) so the\n2601\t    migration's CHECK constraints (`dogpile_events.status` and\n2602\t    `fraud_flags.status`) remain the single source of truth.\n2603\t- **Read-only guarantee**: only `select` statements; no INSERT / UPDATE /\n2604\t  DELETE anywhere. Every dogpile or fraud-flag mutation already lives behind\n2605\t  the FR-14 action ids (`dogpile.cancel`, `fraud_flag.status.update`)\n2606\t  declared in `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts:154-159`, with no\n2607\t  implementation yet (FR-14 framework not built — separate checklist\n2608\t  item).\n2609\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n2610\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n2611\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n2612\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (59 files, 605/605, no regressions)\n2613\t- **Next**: matching frontend `/operations/dogpile` page + fraud-review\n2614\t  surface.\n2615\t- **Log**: iteration-097.log\n2616\t## Iteration 97 — 2026-04-26T06:27:25Z — OK\n2617\t- **Log**: iteration-097.log\n2618\t\n2619\t\n2620\t\n2621\t## Iteration 98 — 2026-04-26 — OK\n2622\t- **Item**: `[frontend] /operations/dogpile (lifecycle + participation) and fraud review surface (page or user-detail section).`\n2623\t- **Files added** (5):\n2624\t  - `peek/app/operations/dogpile/page.tsx` — server-rendered page\n2625\t    composing the FR-4 metric strip + dogpile-events section + fraud-flags\n2626\t    review section. Mirrors the `/economy/challenges` orchestration:\n2627\t    `getPeekActorContext` → `isRouteAllowedForRole` → 2 normalisers →\n2628\t    overview + 2 list queries → existing tables + filter bars. Each\n2629\t    section calls out the read-only boundary in operator-facing copy and\n2630\t    cross-references the FR-14 mutation action ids\n2631\t    (`dogpile.cancel`, `fraud_flag.status.update`).\n2632\t  - `peek/src/lib/operations-dogpile-search-params.ts` — URL-addressable\n2633\t    filter normalisers for the two prefixed param groups\n2634\t    (`dogpFilter*` for dogpile events, `fraudFilter*` for fraud flags).\n2635\t    Empty / whitespace → null; allowlisted enum values pass through;\n2636\t    unknown enum values normalise to null so a stale URL chip cannot lie\n2637\t    about the filter state. Reuses `PEEK_DOGPILE_STATUSES` from\n2638\t    `lib/types/peek.ts` and declares `PEEK_FRAUD_FLAG_STATUSES`\n2639\t    (`open` / `reviewed` / `dismissed`) to match the migration-011\n2640\t    CHECK constraint.\n2641\t  - `peek/src/components/operations-dogpile-filter-bar.tsx` — two\n2642\t    GET-style forms posting back to `/operations/dogpile`. Shared style\n2643\t    block matches the `economy-challenges-filter-bar.tsx` pattern; date\n2644\t    inputs slice to `YYYY-MM-DD`; status selects expose only the\n2645\t    allowlisted values.\n2646\t  - `peek/src/components/dogpile-events-table.tsx` — read-only dense\n2647\t    table over `PeekDogpileEventRow`. Status chip tones:\n2648\t    `scheduled = info`, `active = positive`, `ended = neutral`,\n2649\t    `cancelled = warning`. Multiplier rendered as `2.5×` (column already\n2650\t    text from the NUMERIC(4,2) round-trip). Game-entries and\n2651\t    point-grants counts use `toLocaleString` for thousands separators.\n2652\t    Empty + error states match the rest of the FR-4 table primitives.\n2653\t  - `peek/src/components/fraud-flags-table.tsx` — read-only review\n2654\t    table over `PeekFraudFlagListRow`. Status chip tones:\n2655\t    `open = warning`, `reviewed = info`, `dismissed = neutral`. Username\n2656\t    cell links to `/users/[userId]` with the userId fallback when the\n2657\t    profile join is sparse. JSONB `details` column round-trips verbatim\n2658\t    via `JSON.stringify(..., null, 2)` inside a constrained `<pre>`\n2659\t    block so the operator can paste the full body into a paste bin.\n2660\t- **Read-only guarantee**: no buttons, mutations, or form actions besides\n2661\t  the GET filter forms — every dogpile or fraud-flag write still lives\n2662\t  behind the FR-14 `dogpile.cancel` and `fraud_flag.status.update` action\n2663\t  ids (declared in `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts:154-159` but\n2664\t  unimplemented).\n2665\t- **Auth handling**: page checks `getPeekActorContext()` then\n2666\t  `isRouteAllowedForRole(\"/operations/dogpile\", role)`. Unknown route\n2667\t  prefix falls through to the default rule (any resolved peek role —\n2668\t  `business` or `admin`) per System Invariant #6, matching the existing\n2669\t  `/economy/*` and `/games/*` pages. The `Operations` nav item already\n2670\t  points to `/operations/queue`, which is unbuilt; this page exposes\n2671\t  itself via the FR-4 drilldown links from the dogpile metrics\n2672\t  (`/operations/dogpile?status=…`) defined in iteration 97's\n2673\t  `getDogpileFraudOverview`.\n2674\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n2675\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n2676\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n2677\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (59 files, 605/605, no regressions)\n2678\t- **Next**: matching test pair (`Dogpile + fraud query + page tests for\n2679\t  state transitions, sparse, and read-only enforcement`).\n2680\t- **Log**: iteration-098.log\n2681\t## Iteration 98 — 2026-04-26T06:33:19Z — OK\n2682\t- **Log**: iteration-098.log"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"247526a1-4b21-4707-9ade-4ba9edd09da3","uuid":"a97abb0d-c255-4e22-be58-fd22c5fb6091","timestamp":"2026-04-26T06:33:39.421Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/305-peek-operations-admin/history.md","content":"    iteration 95's 473)\n  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n- **Next**: `[engine] Dogpile + fraud queries` — 7 unchecked items\n  remain in the Implementation Checklist.\n- **Log**: iteration-096.log\n## Iteration 96 — 2026-04-26T06:20:30Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-096.log\n\n\n\n## Iteration 97 — 2026-04-26 — OK\n- **Item**: `[engine] Dogpile + fraud queries: dogpile_events (scheduled/active/ended/cancelled with linked campaigns/game_entries/point_grants) + fraud_flags (open/reviewed/dismissed read-only).`\n- **Files added** (1):\n  - `peek/src/server/db/queries/get-dogpile-and-fraud.ts` — three exports\n    matching the FR-9 read-only contract:\n    - `listDogpileEvents` reads `dogpile_events` with optional `status`\n      ('scheduled' / 'active' / 'ended' / 'cancelled') + `startsFrom` /\n      `startsTo` filters, left-joins `campaigns` for the parent campaign\n      name + type (campaign_id is nullable), and annotates each row with\n      scalar-subquer